Contain the implementation of interfaces and private objects only to be used internally.

          Description

Interface Summary
AsyncExecutor A strategy to define how asynchronous execution is achieved.
For example, on pure Java SE platform, a implementation of AsyncExecutor could use the java.util.concurrent API.
If used on a Android platform, for example, the implementation of AsyncExecutor could use the Android's AsyncTask class.
